# Testing Guide

## Overview

{{ project_name }} uses a layered testing strategy aligned with the hexagonal
architecture.

## Backend Testing

### Test Runner

Tests run through **tox** with **pytest**:

```bash
task backend:test          # Run all tests via tox
task backend:test:unit     # Run unit tests only
task backend:test:coverage # Run with coverage report
```

### Test Structure

```
tests/
+-- conftest.py            # Shared fixtures
+-- factories/             # Test factories
+-- fixtures/              # Reusable fixtures
+-- unit/
|   +-- test_entities.py
|   +-- test_value_objects.py
|   +-- test_services.py
|   +-- test_validators.py
|   +-- test_cache.py
|   +-- test_retry_policies.py
+-- integration/
|   +-- test_api.py
|   +-- test_database.py
+-- property/
|   +-- test_value_objects.py
+-- e2e/
    +-- test_smoke.py
```

### Writing Unit Tests

Test domain logic and use cases in isolation:

```python
from {{ project_slug }}.core.entities.user import User
from {{ project_slug }}.core.value_objects.email import Email


def test_create_user() -> None:
    email = Email("test@example.com")
    user = User(email=email, display_name="Test User")

    assert user.email == email
    assert user.display_name == "Test User"
```

### Writing Integration Tests

Test the full HTTP request/response cycle:

```python
import pytest
from httpx import AsyncClient


@pytest.mark.anyio
async def test_health_endpoint(client: AsyncClient) -> None:
    response = await client.get("/api/v1/health")

    assert response.status_code == 200
    assert response.json()["status"] == "ok"
```

### Property-Based Tests

Use Hypothesis for property-based testing:

```python
from hypothesis import given, strategies as st
from {{ project_slug }}.core.value_objects.email import Email


@given(st.emails())
def test_valid_emails_accepted(email_str: str) -> None:
    email = Email(email_str)
    assert str(email) == email_str.lower().strip()
```

### Coverage

Generate HTML coverage report:

```bash
task backend:test:coverage
open htmlcov/index.html
```

## Frontend Testing

### Unit Tests

Run with vitest:

```bash
task frontend:test         # Run unit tests
task frontend:test:coverage # With coverage
```

Tests are located in `frontend/tests/`.
{% if use_playwright %}

### End-to-End Tests

Run with Playwright:

```bash
task test:e2e              # Run E2E tests headless
task test:e2e:ui           # Run with Playwright UI
```

E2E tests are in `tests/e2e/`.
{% endif %}
